Returns the comma-separated list of property page names declared on a
category, including those inherited from ancestor categories.

Output format: `Property:Has_title,Property:Has_author,Property:Has_isbn`

This is a Tier A primitive — returns data, not markup. Use it to drive
custom display logic without having to learn the inverse-ask +
ancestor-walk pattern yourself.

Parameter:
* category - The category name (without `Category:` prefix)

Example (iterate and render each property's value):
 {{#arraymap:{{Category/effective-properties|category=Book}}|,|@@p@@|
   {{Property/label|prop=@@p@@}}: {{Property/value|prop=@@p@@|page={{FULLPAGENAME}}}}
 |\n}}
</noinclude>
